Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kazuo Aichi, director general of the Defense Agency 
[DA], met with Larson, commander of the U.S. Pacific Command, at 
the Defense Agency on 10 March. During the meeting, he made 
clear that he intends to visit the United States during the 
holiday season that begins at the end of April. He is expected 
to hold his first Japan-U.S. defense summit meeting with U.S. 
Defense Secretary Perry. During the meeting, Commander Larson 
said he will retire in early May. 

